      "type": "text",
      "data": "<div style=\"word-wrap: break-word; -webkit-nbsp-mode: space; -webkit-line-break: after-white-space; white-space: normal;\">\n<div style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">I had no idea how to do the JavaScript equivalent to:</div>\n<div style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">\n<div>    $(window).trigger(&quot;resize&quot;);</div>\n<div><br/>\n<br/></div>\n<div>It is this:</div>\n<div>     var evt = document.createEvent('UIEvents');</div>\n<div>     evt.initUIEvent('resize', true, false,window,0);</div>\n</div>\n<span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">     window.dispatchEvent(evt);</span>\n</div>"
    }
  ]
